1
00:01:08,239 --> 00:01:09,560
Piggy

2
00:01:09,680 --> 00:01:10,359
And you guys...

3
00:01:10,359 --> 00:01:12,040
Just stay inside and be good

4
00:01:12,040 --> 00:01:12,799
Do you hear me?

5
00:01:13,200 --> 00:01:14,439
Eat well

6
00:01:14,439 --> 00:01:15,519
Sleep well

7
00:01:15,519 --> 00:01:16,719
Grow nice and fat

8
00:01:16,719 --> 00:01:18,280
You know? Piggy

9
00:01:29,159 --> 00:01:31,200
Why can't you just speak openly?

10
00:01:31,200 --> 00:01:31,879
What are you hiding from?

11
00:01:33,799 --> 00:01:35,920
My mom wants me to slaughter your pigs

12
00:01:37,120 --> 00:01:38,239
Would you dare?

13
00:01:38,840 --> 00:01:40,560
You're Sister Yingrong, how would I dare?

14
00:01:41,040 --> 00:01:42,000
My second brother would

15
00:01:42,480 --> 00:01:43,599
My second brother is back

16
00:01:45,599 --> 00:01:46,519
Haiyang is back

17
00:01:47,799 --> 00:01:48,359
True

18
00:01:48,359 --> 00:01:49,920
It's been six or seven years, he should be back

19
00:01:50,760 --> 00:01:51,719
Aren't you afraid?

20
00:01:52,439 --> 00:01:52,719
Me?

21
00:01:53,519 --> 00:01:54,519
I'm risking...

22
00:01:54,640 --> 00:01:55,560
betraying my family...

23
00:01:55,560 --> 00:01:56,959
to come and tip you off

24
00:01:57,319 --> 00:01:58,879
But I'm open and above board

25
00:01:58,879 --> 00:01:59,959
What do I have to fear?

26
00:02:01,239 --> 00:02:01,920
Sister Yingrong

27
00:02:02,280 --> 00:02:02,959
Your...

28
00:02:03,239 --> 00:02:03,920
new...

29
00:02:04,760 --> 00:02:05,480
motorcycle

30
00:02:05,560 --> 00:02:06,599
Let me take it for a spin

31
00:02:07,799 --> 00:02:09,759
Look at you, drooling over it

32
00:02:14,000 --> 00:02:16,159
It's not impossible to lend you the bike

33
00:02:16,159 --> 00:02:16,680
Really?

34
00:02:16,680 --> 00:02:17,240
But

35
00:02:17,520 --> 00:02:19,439
Don't go telling your big brother or your mom

36
00:02:19,520 --> 00:02:20,439
that I lent it to you

37
00:02:20,599 --> 00:02:22,280
Lest they think I'm still being nice to you

38
00:02:22,439 --> 00:02:22,960
Take it

39
00:02:24,000 --> 00:02:24,479
Thanks, Sister

40
00:02:24,479 --> 00:02:25,159
Wait a second

41
00:02:26,919 --> 00:02:27,919
In one piece

42
00:02:28,719 --> 00:02:29,360
Definitely

43
00:02:36,039 --> 00:02:37,120
This floor is swept...

44
00:02:37,120 --> 00:02:38,400
quite clean

45
00:02:40,919 --> 00:02:41,599
Uncle Zhu

46
00:02:46,879 --> 00:02:47,520
Uncle Zhu

47
00:02:48,879 --> 00:02:50,840
You watched Haiyang grow up

48
00:02:51,560 --> 00:02:52,400
You know

49
00:02:53,000 --> 00:02:54,000
He's not bad at heart

50
00:02:54,520 --> 00:02:56,159
He was young and didn't know better

51
00:02:56,599 --> 00:02:57,919
He was impulsive and made a mistake

52
00:02:59,360 --> 00:03:00,879
Now that he's out

53
00:03:01,120 --> 00:03:02,719
the road isn't easy to walk

54
00:03:03,919 --> 00:03:05,439
If you could help him

55
00:03:05,759 --> 00:03:06,680
Let him go to your...

56
00:03:06,680 --> 00:03:08,960
carpenter cousin's to learn a trade

57
00:03:12,080 --> 00:03:13,120
that would be the best

58
00:03:19,319 --> 00:03:19,800
Not bad.

59
00:03:20,840 --> 00:03:22,439
Freshly picked Yongchuan Xiùyá green tea.

60
00:03:22,759 --> 00:03:23,759
Pan-fried over a low fire.

61
00:03:25,639 --> 00:03:26,599
This tea is nice.

62
00:03:28,560 --> 00:03:29,639
Today's Chilled Rice Cake...

63
00:03:29,639 --> 00:03:30,680
...I made a bit too much.

64
00:03:30,759 --> 00:03:32,240
I can't finish it all by myself.

65
00:03:32,240 --> 00:03:33,120
It'd be a waste to throw it away.

66
00:03:33,360 --> 00:03:34,280
Hey, Sis Li.

67
00:03:34,439 --> 00:03:34,840
Come over here.

68
00:03:34,840 --> 00:03:36,039
Let's eat together.

69
00:03:36,360 --> 00:03:36,759
Coming.

70
00:03:36,759 --> 00:03:38,000
Let's all have some together.

71
00:03:38,240 --> 00:03:38,919
Come on, come on.

72
00:03:41,159 --> 00:03:42,479
Every day, it's just...

73
00:03:42,479 --> 00:03:43,840
...nothing but the smell of pig manure.

74
00:03:44,199 --> 00:03:44,919
Tell me...

75
00:03:45,400 --> 00:03:47,919
...isn't it wicked to make such a foul mess?

76
00:03:47,919 --> 00:03:48,599
Yeah, exactly.

77
00:03:48,879 --> 00:03:50,000
It stinks so bad.

78
00:03:50,319 --> 00:03:51,879
Even the relatives visiting us...

79
00:03:51,960 --> 00:03:53,000
...can't stand it anymore.

80
00:03:53,319 --> 00:03:54,400
They leave after sitting for just a few minutes.

81
00:03:54,400 --> 00:03:56,319
Lately, the air around here...

82
00:03:56,319 --> 00:03:57,520
...is full of the smell of pig manure.

83
00:03:57,520 --> 00:03:59,159
It stinks to death.

84
00:03:59,159 --> 00:04:00,000
Yeah.

85
00:04:00,479 --> 00:04:01,360
It's too smelly.

86
00:04:02,159 --> 00:04:02,800
Usually in our house...

87
00:04:02,800 --> 00:04:04,039
Auntie Chen.

88
00:04:04,319 --> 00:04:05,360
I just cleaned the pigsty.

89
00:04:05,360 --> 00:04:07,159
Where is the pig manure smell coming from?

90
00:04:07,159 --> 00:04:08,560
The smell of pig manure is everywhere.

91
00:04:08,560 --> 00:04:09,800
You smell like pig manure.

92
00:04:09,800 --> 00:04:11,199
The water you use to wash the pigsty...

93
00:04:11,199 --> 00:04:12,120
...also smells like pig manure.

94
00:04:13,159 --> 00:04:14,039
Does it?

95
00:04:15,199 --> 00:04:16,680
Then I'll clean it more thoroughly.

96
00:04:16,759 --> 00:04:17,920
No matter how clean you make it...

97
00:04:18,079 --> 00:04:19,360
...there's always going to be that...

98
00:04:19,360 --> 00:04:20,000
...smell of pig manure.

99
00:04:21,399 --> 00:04:21,959
Mom.

100
00:04:27,839 --> 00:04:29,199
Can we even live here anymore?

101
00:04:29,560 --> 00:04:30,720
The smell is killing me.

102
00:04:32,199 --> 00:04:33,920
Zheng Haiyang, what are you doing?

103
00:04:34,120 --> 00:04:35,560
My mom said you can't raise pigs.

104
00:04:36,560 --> 00:04:38,120
You come back and just want to cause trouble, right?

105
00:04:38,480 --> 00:04:39,240
In this courtyard...

106
00:04:39,240 --> 00:04:40,279
...your family owns half...

107
00:04:40,279 --> 00:04:41,319
...and my family owns half.

108
00:04:41,319 --> 00:04:42,480
It's not like I'm using your space.

109
00:04:42,480 --> 00:04:43,759
Why can't I raise them?

110
00:04:43,879 --> 00:04:44,439
You choose.

111
00:04:45,319 --> 00:04:46,759
Do I get rid of them, or will you?

112
00:04:49,120 --> 00:04:50,000
These pigs...

113
00:04:50,160 --> 00:04:51,240
...I'm definitely raising them.

114
00:04:53,360 --> 00:04:55,879
Actually, Yingrong keeps it very clean.

115
00:04:55,879 --> 00:04:56,639
Yesterday...

116
00:04:56,639 --> 00:04:59,519
...she even swept up the pig manure in front of my house.

117
00:04:59,519 --> 00:05:00,560
It was her pig...

118
00:05:00,639 --> 00:05:01,560
...that pooped everywhere.

119
00:05:01,759 --> 00:05:02,560
Shouldn't she sweep it up?

120
00:05:02,560 --> 00:05:03,560
She absolutely should sweep it up.

121
00:05:03,879 --> 00:05:05,120
Auntie Chen.

122
00:05:05,240 --> 00:05:07,000
If you hadn't let the pig out...

123
00:05:07,000 --> 00:05:08,879
...would it have pooped everywhere?

124
00:05:08,879 --> 00:05:09,959
Don't you stand there...

125
00:05:09,959 --> 00:05:11,480
...and blame others for everything.

126
00:05:11,600 --> 00:05:12,360
That pig of yours...

127
00:05:12,680 --> 00:05:14,120
...it ran out of the pigsty...

128
00:05:14,120 --> 00:05:14,720
...on its own.

129
00:05:15,079 --> 00:05:16,319
It even knocked me down yesterday.

130
00:05:16,399 --> 00:05:17,439
My poor old back...

131
00:05:17,560 --> 00:05:19,480
...is s-still hurting now.

132
00:05:22,240 --> 00:05:22,839
Mom.

133
00:05:23,600 --> 00:05:24,800
It stinks to death.

134
00:05:25,319 --> 00:05:26,800
Can't a person live?

135
00:05:28,199 --> 00:05:30,079
I'm already looking for a place.

136
00:05:30,079 --> 00:05:32,319
Just give me a little more time.

137
00:05:32,319 --> 00:05:33,160
During this time...

138
00:05:33,160 --> 00:05:34,800
...I'll keep the pigsty clean.

139
00:05:34,800 --> 00:05:35,879
Once I find a place...

140
00:05:35,879 --> 00:05:37,079
...I'll move out.

141
00:05:37,079 --> 00:05:38,160
How much longer will that take?

142
00:05:38,160 --> 00:05:39,079
There's no exact date.

143
00:05:40,639 --> 00:05:42,160
I'll hurry.

144
00:05:43,759 --> 00:05:45,040
I can't breathe.

145
00:05:45,519 --> 00:05:45,839
Mom!

146
00:05:45,839 --> 00:05:46,360
I can't breathe!

147
00:05:47,920 --> 00:05:48,879
You insist on raising them, right?

148
00:05:50,120 --> 00:05:50,639
I can't make it.

149
00:05:50,839 --> 00:05:51,519
Right.

150
00:05:55,160 --> 00:05:56,399
Zheng Haiyang, what are you doing?

151
00:06:30,560 --> 00:06:31,680
This business between your two families...

152
00:06:31,680 --> 00:06:33,240
...you'd better resolve it yourselves.

153
00:06:33,240 --> 00:06:34,279
We're staying out of it.

154
00:06:34,279 --> 00:06:35,920
Yeah, yeah. Let's go, let's go.

155
00:06:46,879 --> 00:06:47,560
Tea leaves

156
00:06:47,920 --> 00:06:49,319
I've put them all in the jar for you

157
00:06:54,120 --> 00:06:54,920
Old Zhu

158
00:06:54,920 --> 00:06:55,519
About Haiyang's matter

159
00:06:55,519 --> 00:06:56,360
Old Zhu! Old Zhu!

160
00:06:57,000 --> 00:06:59,000
You must not agree to help Haiyang

161
00:06:59,519 --> 00:07:00,800
You absolutely must not agree

162
00:07:03,240 --> 00:07:03,800
Uncle

163
00:07:05,360 --> 00:07:07,240
Xiaochuan, can you really do this?

164
00:07:07,240 --> 00:07:09,160
Don't treat me like a rookie

165
00:07:09,360 --> 00:07:11,360
I've been practicing driving all day

166
00:07:11,360 --> 00:07:12,319
Then let's race

167
00:07:12,639 --> 00:07:13,560
Come on

168
00:07:14,399 --> 00:07:15,000
Let's go

169
00:07:21,079 --> 00:07:22,519
Xiaochuan, can you handle it?

170
00:07:22,879 --> 00:07:24,160
Don't let him win

171
00:07:24,360 --> 00:07:25,639
He can't overtake me

172
00:07:40,480 --> 00:07:41,519
You slaughtered their pig

173
00:07:41,800 --> 00:07:43,079
Mom said she couldn't stand the smell

174
00:07:43,160 --> 00:07:43,879
Said it stank so bad

175
00:07:44,279 --> 00:07:45,480
So you actually slaughtered it

176
00:07:47,800 --> 00:07:49,279
I went to great lengths to ask Uncle Zhu

177
00:07:49,279 --> 00:07:50,720
to let you learn a trade

178
00:07:51,319 --> 00:07:52,079
Acting like this

179
00:07:52,439 --> 00:07:53,920
what kind of future will you have?

180
00:07:54,680 --> 00:07:56,560
This isn't his fault

181
00:07:56,560 --> 00:07:58,519
I just couldn't stand it anymore

182
00:07:58,639 --> 00:08:00,240
So I told him to slaughter it

183
00:08:00,519 --> 00:08:01,160
Mom

184
00:08:01,920 --> 00:08:03,319
Didn't I tell you already?

185
00:08:03,639 --> 00:08:05,000
If their pig raising succeeds

186
00:08:05,079 --> 00:08:06,279
our family could do it too

187
00:08:07,079 --> 00:08:07,680
Besides

188
00:08:08,120 --> 00:08:09,480
have you really thought about Haiyang?

189
00:08:10,680 --> 00:08:11,480
He just got out

190
00:08:11,959 --> 00:08:13,279
You making him do something like this

191
00:08:13,800 --> 00:08:14,560
how will the neighbors

192
00:08:14,560 --> 00:08:15,839
get along with him in the future?

193
00:08:15,839 --> 00:08:17,800
I... I just wanted

194
00:08:17,800 --> 00:08:19,399
to scare that family a bit

195
00:08:19,399 --> 00:08:20,639
My life is what it is anyway

196
00:08:21,399 --> 00:08:21,759
You

197
00:08:21,800 --> 00:08:22,839
Who cares what others say?

198
00:08:25,959 --> 00:08:26,920
You'd better think first

199
00:08:27,000 --> 00:08:28,040
about how to pay for the pig

200
00:08:28,600 --> 00:08:30,040
We pay her money?

201
00:08:30,519 --> 00:08:30,800
She

202
00:08:30,959 --> 00:08:32,799
She ruined your marriage plans before

203
00:08:33,080 --> 00:08:34,279
I asked her to return the cash gift

204
00:08:34,440 --> 00:08:35,879
and she still hasn't paid it back

205
00:08:36,039 --> 00:08:36,600
Mom

206
00:08:38,759 --> 00:08:39,759
Do you think this matter

207
00:08:40,039 --> 00:08:41,080
is justifiable?

208
00:08:41,600 --> 00:08:42,679
They were in the wrong to begin with

209
00:08:42,919 --> 00:08:44,440
The neighbors all opposed raising pigs

210
00:08:44,559 --> 00:08:45,559
So what if it's slaughtered?

211
00:08:45,840 --> 00:08:47,120
Let's see what she can do to me

212
00:08:47,559 --> 00:08:48,159
What can she do?

213
00:08:58,799 --> 00:08:59,440
What happened?

214
00:09:01,320 --> 00:09:01,799
Bro

215
00:09:02,200 --> 00:09:02,559
I...

216
00:09:03,679 --> 00:09:05,279
I think I caused a little trouble.

217
00:09:08,200 --> 00:09:09,320
How little is this trouble?

218
00:09:09,759 --> 00:09:10,559
Well...

219
00:09:10,720 --> 00:09:12,600
I crashed Yingrong's bike.

220
00:09:12,919 --> 00:09:14,120
It shouldn't...

221
00:09:14,120 --> 00:09:15,200
be a big deal, right?

222
00:09:17,440 --> 00:09:18,600
You borrowed her bike?

223
00:09:20,120 --> 00:09:21,919
You've never even touched a motorcycle.

224
00:09:22,879 --> 00:09:24,519
Why were you driving her bike?

225
00:09:26,679 --> 00:09:27,279
Now look what you've done.

226
00:09:27,960 --> 00:09:28,799
How do we pay for the pig?

227
00:09:30,360 --> 00:09:31,679
And the bike... how do we pay for that?

228
00:09:34,399 --> 00:09:35,600
Bike, bike, bike.

229
00:09:36,000 --> 00:09:36,799
We're not paying.

230
00:09:37,279 --> 00:09:38,080
The Wang family...

231
00:09:38,320 --> 00:09:39,960
hasn't even paid back our cash gift yet.

232
00:09:40,159 --> 00:09:41,200
Why should we pay?

233
00:09:42,759 --> 00:09:43,440
Zheng Haiyang!

234
00:09:43,519 --> 00:09:44,440
Get out here!

235
00:09:44,559 --> 00:09:45,559
Don't play dead in there!

236
00:09:45,559 --> 00:09:46,120
Come out!

237
00:09:46,759 --> 00:09:48,159
What are you looking at? Open the door!

238
00:09:49,080 --> 00:09:50,279
You better come out right now!

239
00:09:50,279 --> 00:09:51,240
I can see you!

240
00:09:51,279 --> 00:09:52,159
Stop hiding!

241
00:09:53,120 --> 00:09:53,720
Come out!

242
00:09:55,480 --> 00:09:55,759
You!

243
00:09:55,759 --> 00:09:56,159
Yingrong.

244
00:09:57,559 --> 00:09:59,200
A girl like you...

245
00:09:59,399 --> 00:10:00,519
shouting so loud...

246
00:10:00,720 --> 00:10:02,000
aren't you ashamed?

247
00:10:02,159 --> 00:10:03,240
What have I got to be ashamed of?

248
00:10:03,399 --> 00:10:04,759
It's your Zheng family bullying people!

249
00:10:04,759 --> 00:10:06,360
Why did you slaughter my pig?

250
00:10:07,320 --> 00:10:07,840
Yingrong...

251
00:10:07,840 --> 00:10:09,080
This matter is indeed our...

252
00:10:09,519 --> 00:10:10,639
Is that how you talk to your elders?

253
00:10:11,120 --> 00:10:12,120
That pig of yours...

254
00:10:12,320 --> 00:10:13,440
everyone thinks it stinks.

255
00:10:13,559 --> 00:10:14,399
It deserved to be killed.

256
00:10:14,399 --> 00:10:15,320
It deserved to be slaughtered.

257
00:10:15,320 --> 00:10:16,159
So what do you want?

258
00:10:17,000 --> 00:10:18,120
I can't be bothered with you.

259
00:10:19,000 --> 00:10:19,639
Zheng Haiyang.

260
00:10:19,799 --> 00:10:20,320
Speak.

261
00:10:20,360 --> 00:10:21,000
What do we do?

262
00:10:21,559 --> 00:10:22,399
I slaughtered the pig.

263
00:10:22,519 --> 00:10:23,720
Whatever you want, I'm ready.

264
00:10:24,039 --> 00:10:25,440
I'm a grown man, why would I fear you?

265
00:10:25,879 --> 00:10:27,840
Oh, so now you're acting all manly?

266
00:10:27,960 --> 00:10:28,399
Fine.

267
00:10:28,519 --> 00:10:29,600
Then let's go to the Public Security Bureau and clear this up.

268
00:10:29,799 --> 00:10:30,279
Let's go.

269
00:10:30,639 --> 00:10:31,120
Let's go.

270
00:10:32,200 --> 00:10:32,679
Let's go.

271
00:10:33,399 --> 00:10:33,840
Yingrong!

272
00:10:33,879 --> 00:10:34,279
Yingrong!

273
00:10:34,480 --> 00:10:35,360
Don't be rash.

274
00:10:35,720 --> 00:10:36,360
You know...

275
00:10:36,639 --> 00:10:37,360
my brother just got out.

276
00:10:37,360 --> 00:10:38,200
He hasn't reintegrated into society yet.

277
00:10:38,200 --> 00:10:39,320
Give him a chance.

278
00:10:39,919 --> 00:10:41,000
Yeah, Sister Yingrong.

279
00:10:41,000 --> 00:10:42,159
If you report this and the police come...

280
00:10:42,159 --> 00:10:43,360
and my second brother goes back in...

281
00:10:43,360 --> 00:10:44,799
how will he ever turn his life around?

282
00:10:48,679 --> 00:10:49,600
Then pay me.

283
00:10:49,679 --> 00:10:50,480
And apologize to me.

284
00:10:50,799 --> 00:10:51,360
That pig of yours...

285
00:10:51,360 --> 00:10:52,200
was disturbing our lives anyway.

286
00:10:52,200 --> 00:10:53,120
Why should we pay?

287
00:10:53,480 --> 00:10:54,159
You want money? Sure.

288
00:10:54,559 --> 00:10:55,399
I don't have any right now.

289
00:10:57,000 --> 00:10:58,000
I just don't have money.

290
00:10:58,120 --> 00:10:59,080
